1
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:34,320
=Hold a Court Now=

2
00:01:35,260 --> 00:01:38,500
=Episode 4=

3
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:45,610
So what now?

4
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:47,970
We've eaten,
and Xiaolongbao's getting sleepy.

5
00:01:48,120 --> 00:01:49,920
Let's head back to the court?

6
00:01:53,210 --> 00:01:54,410
(Ms. Shu)

7
00:01:57,890 --> 00:01:59,529
Ms. Shu, how is it?

8
00:01:59,530 --> 00:02:00,569
Did you find the child?

9
00:02:00,570 --> 00:02:02,399
Yes. She's fine now.

10
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:04,280
That's good. Where are you?

11
00:02:04,320 --> 00:02:05,809
I'm still in Dongshan District.

12
00:02:05,810 --> 00:02:07,130
Dongshan?

13
00:02:08,040 --> 00:02:09,599
Why are you still at the Forest Park?

14
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:11,210
I'll explain later.

15
00:02:11,250 --> 00:02:12,849
How's Xiaolongbao?

16
00:02:12,850 --> 00:02:13,849
Aixi told me

17
00:02:13,850 --> 00:02:15,849
you're with Ms. Qin taking care of her.

18
00:02:15,850 --> 00:02:17,849
Yes, I'm with Ms. Qin.

19
00:02:17,850 --> 00:02:19,849
It's late. The kid can't hold
out much longer, right?

20
00:02:19,850 --> 00:02:21,330
Is she getting cranky?

21
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:22,800
Not yet.

22
00:02:23,170 --> 00:02:24,640
But she will soon.

23
00:02:24,730 --> 00:02:25,689
Why don't you bring her

24
00:02:25,690 --> 00:02:27,210
over to me?

25
00:02:27,850 --> 00:02:28,969
Don't go through the trouble.

26
00:02:28,970 --> 00:02:30,890
She won't last that long.

27
00:02:31,130 --> 00:02:32,129
How about this,

28
00:02:32,130 --> 00:02:33,319
you and Ms. Qin

29
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:34,759
get a room for Xiaolongbao

30
00:02:34,760 --> 00:02:36,129
so she can rest.

31
00:02:36,130 --> 00:02:37,640
I'll reimburse you later.

32
00:02:38,010 --> 00:02:38,569
No need.

33
00:02:38,570 --> 00:02:40,919
The court won't cover this anyway.

34
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:42,969
Don't worry about it. Just go home.

35
00:02:42,970 --> 00:02:44,599
I'll get them a room.

36
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:45,920
I'm hanging up.

37
00:02:50,730 --> 00:02:52,050
That kid.

38
00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:55,290
Ms. Qin.

39
00:02:55,690 --> 00:02:56,729
I knew there's no such thing

40
00:02:56,730 --> 00:02:58,330
as a free lunch.

41
00:02:59,890 --> 00:03:00,920
Dinner.

42
00:03:02,970 --> 00:03:03,919
And late-night snacks too.

43
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:05,120
Fine.

44
00:03:05,410 --> 00:03:06,680
I'll see it through to the end,

45
00:03:06,730 --> 00:03:08,920
helping all the way.

46
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:10,639
But let's be clear,

47
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:12,479
I must be back
at the firm tomorrow morning.

48
00:03:12,480 --> 00:03:13,759
It's very important.

49
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:15,240
I absolutely can't be late.

50
00:03:15,890 --> 00:03:16,960
Alright.

51
00:03:17,130 --> 00:03:18,520
I'll come pick you up

52
00:03:18,690 --> 00:03:19,919
before 8 AM tomorrow.

53
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:21,210
Thank you.

54
00:03:29,730 --> 00:03:31,730
We're here, Xiaolongbao.

55
00:03:34,450 --> 00:03:35,409
Xiezhi will carry you.

56
00:03:35,410 --> 00:03:37,610
Come on, Xiaolongbao, we're here.

57
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:38,919
I'll carry you.

58
00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:40,170
Let's go.

59
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:42,249
Look.

60
00:03:42,250 --> 00:03:45,010
Look, the hotel's beautiful, right?

61
00:03:49,890 --> 00:03:51,010
Hello.

62
00:03:51,150 --> 00:03:52,900
I booked a room online.

63
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,050
Your ID, please.

64
00:03:57,660 --> 00:03:58,319
Look at the lights.

65
00:03:58,320 --> 00:03:59,800
Hello, please wait a moment.

66
00:04:00,010 --> 00:04:01,400
Why aren't you giving it?

67
00:04:01,570 --> 00:04:03,169
You're not staying here?

68
00:04:03,170 --> 00:04:05,330
I live nearby. I'll go home.

69
00:04:06,890 --> 00:04:08,330
The room's already paid for.

70
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:11,290
That's not what I meant.

71
00:04:11,890 --> 00:04:12,729
I'm busy too.

72
00:04:12,730 --> 00:04:15,210
I need to get
to the firm early tomorrow.

73
00:04:15,640 --> 00:04:18,280
I'll pick you up

74
00:04:18,370 --> 00:04:20,080
at 7:50 AM tomorrow.

75
00:04:20,890 --> 00:04:22,040
Alright.

76
00:04:23,960 --> 00:04:25,129
Come, Xiaolongbao.

77
00:04:25,130 --> 00:04:25,839
We're here.

78
00:04:25,840 --> 00:04:26,930
We're here.

79
00:04:27,490 --> 00:04:28,719
Xiaolongbao, look.

80
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:30,690
The room is so big.

81
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:32,890
Come here.

82
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:35,079
Let me take this off first.

83
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:36,839
You've been carrying it all day, right?

84
00:04:36,840 --> 00:04:37,960
Here.

85
00:04:40,570 --> 00:04:41,840
Xiaolongbao,

86
00:04:42,160 --> 00:04:44,249
be good and sleep with Rui.

87
00:04:44,250 --> 00:04:46,040
I will pick you up early tomorrow.

88
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:50,839
Why are you crying, Xiaolongbao?

89
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:53,250
I'm here with you, right?

90
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:54,519
I'm right here with you.

91
00:04:54,520 --> 00:04:56,330
You don't want me to leave?

92
00:04:58,690 --> 00:04:59,959
Don't cry, Xiaolongbao.

93
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:01,449
There are people staying next door.

94
00:05:01,450 --> 00:05:03,640
If you cry, you'll wake them up, okay?

95
00:05:04,320 --> 00:05:06,400
Let me tell you, there's a big bad wolf.

96
00:05:06,450 --> 00:05:08,369
If it hears a child crying,

97
00:05:08,370 --> 00:05:09,279
it'll come.

98
00:05:09,280 --> 00:05:10,159
Don't cry.

99
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:12,160
Don't scare her, okay?

100
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:14,049
Then what do we do now?

101
00:05:14,050 --> 00:05:15,840
I came to help, but now

102
00:05:15,930 --> 00:05:17,480
I don't even know what to do.

103
00:05:18,930 --> 00:05:20,280
How about this,

104
00:05:20,760 --> 00:05:22,890
I tell you a story, okay?

105
00:05:25,890 --> 00:05:28,600
Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs?

106
00:05:30,810 --> 00:05:32,640
The Three Little Pigs?

107
00:05:36,570 --> 00:05:37,960
Nezha Conquers the Sea?

108
00:05:39,050 --> 00:05:39,959
Want to hear?

109
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:41,279
You want that one?

110
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:41,889
Alright.

111
00:05:41,890 --> 00:05:42,930
How about this,

112
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:44,449
let Rui take you to wash up first.

113
00:05:44,450 --> 00:05:45,399
After that,

114
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:47,480
I will tell you the story
of Nezha Conquers the Sea.

115
00:05:47,640 --> 00:05:48,569
Alright, come on.

116
00:05:48,570 --> 00:05:50,330
I will take you to wash up.

117
00:05:50,640 --> 00:05:51,609
Good girl, such a good girl.

118
00:05:51,610 --> 00:05:52,810
So well-behaved.

119
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:54,930
Let's go wash up.

120
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:56,609
Get nice and clean,

121
00:05:56,610 --> 00:05:58,960
then we'll hear a story, okay?

122
00:05:59,370 --> 00:06:01,009
Why are you crying, Xiaolongbao?

123
00:06:01,010 --> 00:06:02,600
Tell me.

124
00:06:07,610 --> 00:06:10,000
(Nezha Conquers the Sea: "Returning bones
to the father, returning flesh to the mother")

125
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:12,249
Long ago, there was a man named Li Jing.

126
00:06:12,250 --> 00:06:15,689
His wife carried the child
for three years and six months

127
00:06:15,690 --> 00:06:17,399
before giving birth to a boy

128
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:18,249
named Nezha.

129
00:06:18,250 --> 00:06:19,569
One year,

130
00:06:19,570 --> 00:06:21,519
there was no rain at all.

131
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:24,159
The people began praying for rain.

132
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:25,959
But the Dragon King
of the East Sea demanded

133
00:06:25,960 --> 00:06:28,600
a boy and a girl as offerings.

134
00:06:28,690 --> 00:06:30,569
After Nezha learned of this,

135
00:06:30,570 --> 00:06:32,010
to save the people,

136
00:06:32,130 --> 00:06:34,279
he fought Ao Bing,

137
00:06:34,280 --> 00:06:35,720
the Dragon King's third son.

138
00:06:35,890 --> 00:06:38,770
In the end,
Nezha tore out his dragon tendon

139
00:06:39,160 --> 00:06:40,810
and brought disaster upon himself.

140
00:06:41,490 --> 00:06:43,319
If this happened today,

141
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:45,319
it would be considered
a fight between minors.

142
00:06:45,320 --> 00:06:47,160
We absolutely must not learn from that.

143
00:06:47,570 --> 00:06:48,839
What are you talking about?

144
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:50,400
How is that just a fight?

145
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:51,369
Wasn't Nezha

146
00:06:51,370 --> 00:06:53,199
standing up for justice
and protecting the people?

147
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:55,079
Which law says
that standing up for justice

148
00:06:55,080 --> 00:06:57,570
means you can intentionally
harm someone?

149
00:06:58,050 --> 00:06:59,929
But he was protecting the people.

150
00:06:59,930 --> 00:07:01,519
That counts as self-defense, doesn't it?

151
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:03,399
At most, self-defense
means stopping someone.

152
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:05,280
You tore out his dragon tendon.

153
00:07:05,490 --> 00:07:07,279
That's excessive self-defense.

154
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:08,889
He should be punished.

155
00:07:08,890 --> 00:07:11,280
Sure, but don't only
talk about punishment.

156
00:07:11,320 --> 00:07:12,279
Why not mention

157
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:14,690
that he also saved
all the people of Chentang Pass?

158
00:07:14,830 --> 00:07:16,759
He returned his bones
to his father and flesh to his mother,

159
00:07:16,760 --> 00:07:18,079
saved so many lives,

160
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:19,639
and still upheld
his duty to his parents.

161
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:21,600
It wasn't easy for Nezha.

162
00:07:22,010 --> 00:07:22,809
As a lawyer,

163
00:07:22,810 --> 00:07:24,609
aren't you being a bit
too rigid in how you see this?

164
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:25,689
Yes,

165
00:07:25,690 --> 00:07:27,319
even if I am a bit rigid,

166
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:28,449
you also said

167
00:07:28,450 --> 00:07:30,249
Nezha is a minor.

168
00:07:30,250 --> 00:07:31,959
Did his parents fulfill their duty

169
00:07:31,960 --> 00:07:33,480
to raise and guide him?

170
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:38,839
How much did Nezha
pay you as legal fees?

171
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:40,759
What does that have to do
with legal fees?

172
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:41,689
Just answer me,

173
00:07:41,690 --> 00:07:43,520
did his parents fulfill
their duty to raise him?

174
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:46,280
Forget it, I can't get through to you.

175
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:47,809
You grew up pampered,

176
00:07:47,810 --> 00:07:49,520
you don't understand real hardship.

177
00:07:50,810 --> 00:07:51,569
The way you put it,

178
00:07:51,570 --> 00:07:53,720
you've experienced
all of life's hardships, huh?

179
00:07:55,450 --> 00:07:57,570
That's not what I meant. I mean...

180
00:07:58,810 --> 00:07:59,719
Xiang.

181
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:00,890
Grandma.

182
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:03,770
Why is there someone behind you?

183
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:05,330
Where's your face?

184
00:08:07,490 --> 00:08:08,839
Didn't I tell you already,

185
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:10,159
don't call me Xiang anymore?

186
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:11,809
Why are you still calling me that?

187
00:08:11,810 --> 00:08:14,130
Who's that behind you?

188
00:08:15,320 --> 00:08:17,770
I... Was there someone behind me just now?

189
00:08:18,840 --> 00:08:20,129
That was Aunt Cao, right?

190
00:08:20,130 --> 00:08:21,450
Aunt Cao?

191
00:08:22,250 --> 00:08:24,489
Did you receive
the medicine I sent Grandma?

192
00:08:24,490 --> 00:08:25,639
Urine?

193
00:08:25,640 --> 00:08:27,570
My urine's fine.

194
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:28,719
Blood is fine too.

195
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:30,930
Aunt Cao just checked me.

196
00:08:31,320 --> 00:08:33,840
Not urine, I meant medicine.

197
00:08:33,920 --> 00:08:35,080
Medicine.

198
00:08:35,130 --> 00:08:36,530
Grandma's medicine.

199
00:08:36,970 --> 00:08:38,240
Aunt Cao,

200
00:08:38,680 --> 00:08:40,799
I sent Grandma's medicine
to the convenience store.

201
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:41,969
Did you get it?

202
00:08:41,970 --> 00:08:43,210
Let me take this.

203
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:45,009
We got it, Xiang.

204
00:08:45,010 --> 00:08:45,919
Yes, we received it.

205
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:48,209
That's why we had your grandma call you.

206
00:08:48,210 --> 00:08:50,759
Then how were Grandma's results

207
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:52,279
from her recent checkup?

208
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:53,799
Not bad.

209
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:56,290
Just a bit of liver fibrosis.

210
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:57,679
At her age,

211
00:08:57,680 --> 00:08:59,840
keeping it under control
like this is already good.

212
00:09:00,490 --> 00:09:01,760
That's good.

213
00:09:01,970 --> 00:09:04,039
The medicine won't stop.

214
00:09:04,040 --> 00:09:04,889
Don't worry.

215
00:09:04,890 --> 00:09:06,279
Tell Grandma not to worry either.

216
00:09:06,280 --> 00:09:08,249
She must take the medicine
on time and in the right dosage.

217
00:09:08,250 --> 00:09:10,960
Once this month's supply is finished,
I'll send the next batch on time next month.

218
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:12,840
Don't worry, Xiang.

219
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:13,889
Alright.

220
00:09:13,890 --> 00:09:15,570
Say less.

221
00:09:16,130 --> 00:09:19,000
Xiang, take care of yourself.

222
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:20,840
Don't just focus on saving money.

223
00:09:21,210 --> 00:09:22,639
Got it, Grandma.

224
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:25,290
You all get some rest. Bye.

225
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:26,880
Suddenly,

226
00:09:27,370 --> 00:09:28,760
with a loud bang,

227
00:09:28,890 --> 00:09:30,369
a figure leapt up.

228
00:09:30,370 --> 00:09:32,690
Tall and imposing,

229
00:09:33,330 --> 00:09:35,530
it was Nezha reborn.

230
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:37,650
Nezha had come back to life.

231
00:09:37,800 --> 00:09:40,120
Master Taiyi then bestowed upon Nezha

232
00:09:40,130 --> 00:09:43,760
the Fire-tipped Spear
and Wind Fire Wheels,

233
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:47,369
and taught him the transformation
of three heads and six arms.

234
00:09:47,370 --> 00:09:49,279
With these treasures,

235
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:50,969
Nezha returned to the East Sea,

236
00:09:50,970 --> 00:09:52,480
majestic and unstoppable.

237
00:09:52,520 --> 00:09:55,080
He defeated the Dragon Kings
of the Four Seas in one stroke.

238
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:57,360
From then on, the Dragon Kings

239
00:09:57,560 --> 00:09:59,530
could no longer harm the people.

240
00:09:59,920 --> 00:10:01,170
The world

241
00:10:01,250 --> 00:10:03,360
was blessed with favorable weather.

242
00:10:03,850 --> 00:10:05,570
Everyone called Nezha

243
00:10:05,850 --> 00:10:07,450
a young hero.

244
00:11:13,130 --> 00:11:14,009
Hello, Mom.

245
00:11:14,010 --> 00:11:15,290
Where are you?

246
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:16,009
Come home tonight.

247
00:11:16,010 --> 00:11:18,210
You need to drive
and pick up Grandpa tomorrow.

248
00:11:18,750 --> 00:11:21,040
I'm over at Jinshu Garden.
I'm heading back now.

249
00:11:21,690 --> 00:11:24,120
Jinshu Garden? What are you doing there?

250
00:11:24,410 --> 00:11:26,410
Something came up at work.
It's all taken care of.

251
00:11:27,490 --> 00:11:28,759
Where's Dad?

252
00:11:28,760 --> 00:11:29,960
He...

253
00:11:30,250 --> 00:11:31,600
He's here.

254
00:11:33,410 --> 00:11:34,529
My car's here.

255
00:11:34,530 --> 00:11:36,250
I'll hang up. I'll be there soon.

256
00:12:10,250 --> 00:12:11,530
Son,

257
00:12:12,170 --> 00:12:13,530
you're back.

258
00:12:13,650 --> 00:12:14,929
Don't rush off.

259
00:12:14,930 --> 00:12:16,130
Have some soup.

260
00:12:17,410 --> 00:12:19,010
Your dad's asleep.

261
00:12:29,810 --> 00:12:31,050
Here,

262
00:12:31,130 --> 00:12:32,530
have some fish soup.

263
00:12:37,810 --> 00:12:39,730
You made it. It smells great.

264
00:12:39,850 --> 00:12:41,050
Drink up.

265
00:12:41,850 --> 00:12:43,730
How's work been lately?

266
00:12:44,330 --> 00:12:45,649
See,

267
00:12:45,650 --> 00:12:47,569
isn't it more comfortable
living at home?

268
00:12:47,570 --> 00:12:49,610
Why go out and make life harder?

269
00:12:51,010 --> 00:12:51,929
As for your dad,

270
00:12:51,930 --> 00:12:53,529
I'll talk to him later.

271
00:12:53,530 --> 00:12:54,649
He shouldn't act like a professor

272
00:12:54,650 --> 00:12:57,130
at home all day.

273
00:12:57,490 --> 00:12:58,809
Mom, it's fine.

274
00:12:58,810 --> 00:13:01,449
Where I live now
is very close to the court.

275
00:13:01,450 --> 00:13:02,650
I can just walk there.

276
00:13:02,850 --> 00:13:05,169
I can even think about work on the way.

277
00:13:05,170 --> 00:13:06,369
Alright.

278
00:13:06,370 --> 00:13:08,130
You have to pick up Grandpa tomorrow.

279
00:13:08,210 --> 00:13:10,810
Stay home tonight. Don't leave.

280
00:13:11,570 --> 00:13:14,250
Why argue with your dad?

281
00:13:15,170 --> 00:13:17,010
I'm not arguing with him.

282
00:13:18,330 --> 00:13:19,890
I just don't understand

283
00:13:20,050 --> 00:13:21,609
why he has to interfere

284
00:13:21,610 --> 00:13:23,570
in everything I do.

285
00:13:23,930 --> 00:13:25,169
Even when I went to the family court,

286
00:13:25,170 --> 00:13:26,769
he kept asking about

287
00:13:26,770 --> 00:13:28,329
my situation every few days.

288
00:13:28,330 --> 00:13:30,009
Your dad asking you

289
00:13:30,010 --> 00:13:31,729
is because he cares about you.

290
00:13:31,730 --> 00:13:33,010
Cares?

291
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:34,369
I think

292
00:13:34,370 --> 00:13:36,049
he's worried I won't
meet his expectations,

293
00:13:36,050 --> 00:13:37,490
that I'm not trying hard enough.

294
00:13:37,610 --> 00:13:38,810
What's wrong?

295
00:13:40,210 --> 00:13:41,890
I want you to improve.

296
00:13:42,490 --> 00:13:43,850
Is that wrong?

297
00:13:46,410 --> 00:13:48,369
Look at you now,

298
00:13:48,370 --> 00:13:49,930
at home,

299
00:13:50,090 --> 00:13:51,450
everything's handed to you.

300
00:13:51,970 --> 00:13:53,649
Your mom takes such good care of you,

301
00:13:53,650 --> 00:13:55,050
you're living comfortably.

302
00:13:55,170 --> 00:13:56,889
Even if you move out,

303
00:13:56,890 --> 00:13:59,289
aren't you still eating
at the cafeteria or ordering takeout?

304
00:13:59,290 --> 00:14:00,369
Besides,

305
00:14:00,370 --> 00:14:02,730
what do you mean
by meeting my expectations?

306
00:14:02,770 --> 00:14:04,049
You're a judge.

307
00:14:04,050 --> 00:14:06,490
You need to meet
the organization's expectations.

308
00:14:06,690 --> 00:14:09,849
Right now, you're just being assigned
to a grassroots court for experience.

309
00:14:09,850 --> 00:14:11,329
It's not like you've been exiled

310
00:14:11,330 --> 00:14:12,850
from the capital
to some remote frontier.

311
00:14:12,930 --> 00:14:13,889
Right.

312
00:14:13,890 --> 00:14:15,930
I think you're absolutely right.

313
00:14:16,050 --> 00:14:18,209
Qingcheng Court
really isn't tough enough.

314
00:14:18,210 --> 00:14:19,729
Next year I'll apply

315
00:14:19,730 --> 00:14:22,370
to be transferred to a rural court
deep in the mountains.

316
00:14:28,890 --> 00:14:30,489
Since you've already avoided it,

317
00:14:30,490 --> 00:14:32,930
why not avoid it all the way?

318
00:15:07,490 --> 00:15:08,849
Xiaolongbao is about to wake up.

319
00:15:08,850 --> 00:15:10,570
I can't be late for work.

320
00:15:13,330 --> 00:15:14,610
Xiaolongbao,

321
00:15:17,410 --> 00:15:18,890
wake up, okay?

322
00:15:19,930 --> 00:15:21,810
This is really not easy for us.

323
00:15:30,690 --> 00:15:34,530
(Qin Rui)

324
00:15:37,010 --> 00:15:40,210
(Shen Xiezhi (Judge))

325
00:15:51,290 --> 00:15:52,810
Will this work?

326
00:15:54,130 --> 00:15:55,329
Xiaolongbao,

327
00:15:55,330 --> 00:15:57,290
let's leave your hair down, okay?

328
00:16:03,770 --> 00:16:04,449
Morning.

329
00:16:04,450 --> 00:16:05,730
Why aren't you ready yet?

330
00:16:06,690 --> 00:16:08,690
I'm fixing her hair.

331
00:16:08,890 --> 00:16:11,090
Xiaolongbao, I'm here to pick you up.

332
00:16:13,250 --> 00:16:14,730
You do it then.

333
00:16:15,490 --> 00:16:17,329
I'm a guy, how would I know how?

334
00:16:17,330 --> 00:16:19,570
I don't know how either,
that's why I asked you to help.

335
00:16:20,570 --> 00:16:22,010
You don't know how to do hair?

336
00:16:24,450 --> 00:16:26,210
Didn't your mom teach you
when you were little?

337
00:16:30,010 --> 00:16:31,250
No.

338
00:16:36,970 --> 00:16:38,970
Did I say something wrong?

339
00:16:40,010 --> 00:16:42,570
You're the Pacific Ocean now,
Judge Shen, meddling in everything?

340
00:16:42,890 --> 00:16:43,369
What's wrong?

341
00:16:43,370 --> 00:16:44,729
Are you going to mediate

342
00:16:44,730 --> 00:16:46,210
my family issues here too?

343
00:16:48,610 --> 00:16:50,049
Take it easy.

344
00:16:50,050 --> 00:16:51,769
Conflicts between children and parents

345
00:16:51,770 --> 00:16:53,370
aren't a big deal.

346
00:16:53,450 --> 00:16:55,370
I don't get along with my dad either.

347
00:16:56,050 --> 00:16:57,330
Really?

348
00:16:57,370 --> 00:16:58,930
What's going on
between you and your dad?

349
00:17:00,370 --> 00:17:01,730
Nothing much.

350
00:17:02,130 --> 00:17:04,369
He just loves telling me
how to do my job.

351
00:17:04,370 --> 00:17:07,010
The older he gets,
the more he acts like a teacher.

352
00:17:08,130 --> 00:17:09,689
Alright, Judge Shen,

353
00:17:09,690 --> 00:17:11,169
don't discuss whether seafood is fresh

354
00:17:11,170 --> 00:17:13,690
with someone who can't even
afford a full meal.

355
00:17:13,930 --> 00:17:14,929
Hurry up.

356
00:17:14,930 --> 00:17:17,130
We still have to go earn a living
at your court at nine.

357
00:17:17,690 --> 00:17:18,809
Alright.

358
00:17:18,810 --> 00:17:19,970
Looks pretty good.

359
00:17:24,290 --> 00:17:25,849
But somehow it still feels off.

360
00:17:25,850 --> 00:17:26,969
It was tight just now,

361
00:17:26,970 --> 00:17:28,369
why does it feel loose again?

362
00:17:28,370 --> 00:17:30,209
Come, Xiaolongbao, over here.

363
00:17:30,210 --> 00:17:31,850
Let me tighten it for you.

364
00:17:32,330 --> 00:17:34,090
How could it be loose?

365
00:17:35,930 --> 00:17:37,050
It hurts?

366
00:17:37,370 --> 00:17:39,369
Alright, you're pulling her hair.

367
00:17:39,370 --> 00:17:40,329
We're not filming today.

368
00:17:40,330 --> 00:17:41,289
It looks fine.

369
00:17:41,290 --> 00:17:42,249
No.

370
00:17:42,250 --> 00:17:43,329
It still looks off to me.

371
00:17:43,330 --> 00:17:44,849
Even if I didn't do her hair perfectly,

372
00:17:44,850 --> 00:17:46,249
I have to show people

373
00:17:46,250 --> 00:17:48,329
that I'm not only

374
00:17:48,330 --> 00:17:49,929
good at winning cases,

375
00:17:49,930 --> 00:17:52,009
but also great at extra service,

376
00:17:52,010 --> 00:17:53,290
right?

377
00:17:54,250 --> 00:17:56,969
You've got quite
a variety of extra services.

378
00:17:56,970 --> 00:17:58,210
Ms. Qin.

379
00:18:08,210 --> 00:18:09,450
This is...

380
00:18:09,850 --> 00:18:12,649
This is a judge
from Qingcheng Court's family division,

381
00:18:12,650 --> 00:18:13,770
Judge Shen.

382
00:18:16,530 --> 00:18:18,010
Hello.

383
00:18:18,650 --> 00:18:19,329
Hello.

384
00:18:19,330 --> 00:18:21,369
Nice to meet you.

385
00:18:21,370 --> 00:18:21,849
An honor.

386
00:18:21,850 --> 00:18:23,410
My name is Zhou Xiaofu.

387
00:18:24,690 --> 00:18:26,770
He's my client.

388
00:18:27,250 --> 00:18:29,170
A prospective client.
We haven't signed yet.

389
00:18:29,850 --> 00:18:31,610
No cooperation agreement yet.

390
00:18:33,690 --> 00:18:35,929
What do you mean prospective client?
A client is a client.

391
00:18:35,930 --> 00:18:37,209
I'll definitely give you that case.

392
00:18:37,210 --> 00:18:38,889
A man's word is his bond.

393
00:18:38,890 --> 00:18:39,769
You see,

394
00:18:39,770 --> 00:18:41,409
lawyers,

395
00:18:41,410 --> 00:18:42,409
they're just very meticulous,

396
00:18:42,410 --> 00:18:44,089
so everything has to be in writing.

397
00:18:44,090 --> 00:18:45,770
I'll send you the contract later.

398
00:18:46,970 --> 00:18:48,409
Mr. Zhou, sorry,
we have something to do.

399
00:18:48,410 --> 00:18:49,369
We need to get going.

400
00:18:49,370 --> 00:18:51,090
We'll talk about the contract later.

401
00:18:51,250 --> 00:18:52,489
Alright, you go ahead.

402
00:18:52,490 --> 00:18:54,849
Judge Shen, please take extra care
with my case when the time comes.

403
00:18:54,850 --> 00:18:56,850
Let's go, Xiaolongbao. Let's go first.

404
00:18:57,610 --> 00:18:59,249
Wait, what's going on?

405
00:18:59,250 --> 00:19:00,730
I haven't gotten my deposit back yet.

406
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:07,609
You arranged for
that person to come, didn't you?

407
00:19:07,610 --> 00:19:09,690
What do you mean I arranged it?

408
00:19:09,970 --> 00:19:11,649
It was a coincidence,
purely a coincidence.

409
00:19:11,650 --> 00:19:12,889
What are the odds?

410
00:19:12,890 --> 00:19:14,649
You stayed here for one night,

411
00:19:14,650 --> 00:19:16,849
we just happened to show up,

412
00:19:16,850 --> 00:19:17,769
and we run into him?

413
00:19:17,770 --> 00:19:18,480
What are you implying?

414
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:19,889
That I deliberately invited him

415
00:19:19,890 --> 00:19:20,849
to bump into you

416
00:19:20,850 --> 00:19:22,449
and use you as a walking advertisement?

417
00:19:22,450 --> 00:19:23,929
You said that, not me.

418
00:19:23,930 --> 00:19:26,089
Why do you think so badly of me?

419
00:19:26,090 --> 00:19:28,810
Last night, you were the one
begging me to come help.

420
00:19:29,610 --> 00:19:30,489
Fine.

421
00:19:30,490 --> 00:19:32,770
Thank you for your cooperation.

422
00:19:32,850 --> 00:19:34,330
Your part is done.

423
00:19:34,410 --> 00:19:35,770
Xiaolongbao, let's go.

424
00:19:36,210 --> 00:19:37,370
Wait...

425
00:19:38,930 --> 00:19:40,490
What do you mean by that?

426
00:19:44,570 --> 00:19:45,289
You two had a fight?

427
00:19:45,290 --> 00:19:46,530
Checking out.

428
00:19:47,130 --> 00:19:48,209
Is he your husband or boyfriend?

429
00:19:48,210 --> 00:19:49,249
Is that child yours?

430
00:19:49,250 --> 00:19:50,610
What are you talking about?

431
00:19:50,730 --> 00:19:52,240
We're not married,
and we're not a couple.

432
00:19:52,240 --> 00:19:53,250
Don't make things up.

433
00:19:53,770 --> 00:19:56,289
I get it. Is it that kind of relationship
between a judge and a lawyer...

434
00:19:56,290 --> 00:19:58,490
Mr. Zhou, I'm quite busy right now.

435
00:19:58,610 --> 00:20:00,249
We'll talk about
the contract later, alright?

436
00:20:00,250 --> 00:20:01,329
All set?

437
00:20:01,330 --> 00:20:01,849
Thank you.

438
00:20:01,850 --> 00:20:02,849
Alright, we'll talk later.

439
00:20:02,850 --> 00:20:03,969
I'll wait for your call.

440
00:20:03,970 --> 00:20:05,330
Or your message.

441
00:20:08,090 --> 00:20:09,850
Are those three a family?

442
00:20:11,290 --> 00:20:12,490
Judge Shen.

443
00:20:15,090 --> 00:20:16,249
No, Judge Shen,

444
00:20:16,250 --> 00:20:18,209
weren't you giving me
a ride back to the firm?

445
00:20:18,210 --> 00:20:19,410
Judge Shen...

446
00:20:19,970 --> 00:20:21,170
Wait,

447
00:20:21,370 --> 00:20:22,730
what do you mean?

448
00:20:46,570 --> 00:20:48,850
(She deliberately brought
that client here.)

449
00:20:49,170 --> 00:20:50,930
(Scheming like that.)

450
00:20:51,090 --> 00:20:52,810
(Even using a child.)

451
00:20:53,490 --> 00:20:54,890
(Would she really do that?)

452
00:21:10,250 --> 00:21:10,889
Mr. He.

453
00:21:10,890 --> 00:21:12,010
Hello.

454
00:21:15,010 --> 00:21:16,090
Come in.

455
00:21:16,890 --> 00:21:17,889
Shu Jing.

456
00:21:17,890 --> 00:21:18,930
Mr. He.

457
00:21:21,810 --> 00:21:24,050
I heard about what happened.

458
00:21:24,170 --> 00:21:25,810
How are you? Are you alright?

459
00:21:25,850 --> 00:21:26,809
I'm fine.

460
00:21:26,810 --> 00:21:28,289
I was overly anxious.

461
00:21:28,290 --> 00:21:29,249
Just a false alarm.

462
00:21:29,250 --> 00:21:30,930
Sorry for causing trouble for everyone.

463
00:21:31,130 --> 00:21:33,449
A child's safety always comes first.

464
00:21:33,450 --> 00:21:35,690
Even being overly cautious
is understandable.

465
00:21:35,770 --> 00:21:36,769
By the way,

466
00:21:36,770 --> 00:21:39,090
I heard Tong is about
to be discharged, right?

467
00:21:39,490 --> 00:21:41,009
I was thinking about it yesterday.

468
00:21:41,010 --> 00:21:42,209
I checked.

469
00:21:42,210 --> 00:21:43,370
It should be soon.

470
00:21:44,010 --> 00:21:45,209
Do you want me

471
00:21:45,210 --> 00:21:46,930
to look into her current situation?

472
00:21:48,050 --> 00:21:48,929
It's fine.

473
00:21:48,930 --> 00:21:50,850
Nothing has happened yet.

474
00:21:50,970 --> 00:21:52,529
Since the hospital is letting her go,

475
00:21:52,530 --> 00:21:54,970
it means she's not as extreme as before.

476
00:21:55,170 --> 00:21:57,129
Let's not trouble the other department.

477
00:21:57,130 --> 00:21:59,010
I'll just keep a closer eye on Fei.

478
00:22:00,210 --> 00:22:01,649
Alright, that works.

479
00:22:01,650 --> 00:22:02,929
But on your side,

480
00:22:02,930 --> 00:22:03,849
if you need anything,

481
00:22:03,850 --> 00:22:05,370
just tell me anytime.

482
00:22:11,250 --> 00:22:12,530
Have another bite.

483
00:22:13,930 --> 00:22:15,210
Good girl.

484
00:22:18,850 --> 00:22:20,529
Why are you called Xiaolongbao?

485
00:22:20,530 --> 00:22:22,570
Is it because you
really love soup dumplings?

486
00:22:23,330 --> 00:22:24,490
Yes.

487
00:22:24,970 --> 00:22:26,089
Then,

488
00:22:26,090 --> 00:22:27,929
which ones do you like?

489
00:22:27,930 --> 00:22:30,050
The ones here or homemade?

490
00:22:30,130 --> 00:22:31,650
My grandma's.

491
00:22:31,850 --> 00:22:33,290
Your grandma makes them?

492
00:22:34,050 --> 00:22:35,850
Do you go to her place often?

493
00:22:37,770 --> 00:22:39,130
Do you miss her?

494
00:22:40,130 --> 00:22:41,649
We've already told her.

495
00:22:41,650 --> 00:22:43,009
She'll be here soon.

496
00:22:43,010 --> 00:22:44,210
Are you happy?

497
00:22:44,330 --> 00:22:45,329
Happy.

498
00:22:45,330 --> 00:22:46,730
Then have another bite.

499
00:22:48,330 --> 00:22:49,570
Good girl.

500
00:22:50,890 --> 00:22:52,130
This way, please.

501
00:22:52,890 --> 00:22:54,290
Xiaolongbao.

502
00:22:54,570 --> 00:22:55,649
Grandma.

503
00:22:55,650 --> 00:22:56,409
Sweetheart, come here.

504
00:22:56,410 --> 00:22:57,129
Grandma.

505
00:22:57,130 --> 00:22:59,329
- Sweetheart, Grandma's here.
- Grandma.

506
00:22:59,330 --> 00:23:00,689
My precious.

507
00:23:00,690 --> 00:23:02,330
Sweetheart.

508
00:23:02,410 --> 00:23:04,130
How could those heartless people,

509
00:23:04,490 --> 00:23:05,609
bring themselves

510
00:23:05,610 --> 00:23:07,490
to leave our child here like this?

511
00:23:08,970 --> 00:23:10,649
My precious.

512
00:23:10,650 --> 00:23:11,809
It's alright now.

513
00:23:11,810 --> 00:23:13,530
My precious.

514
00:23:15,570 --> 00:23:17,570
I'm so sorry, young man.

515
00:23:18,370 --> 00:23:20,730
My blood pressure's
been high these days,

516
00:23:21,130 --> 00:23:22,889
and my headaches came back.

517
00:23:22,890 --> 00:23:25,369
I was on an IV
at the hospital last night.

518
00:23:25,370 --> 00:23:28,010
My old phone ran out of battery,

519
00:23:28,050 --> 00:23:29,729
and there was nowhere to charge it.

520
00:23:29,730 --> 00:23:31,009
I only got home this morning.

521
00:23:31,010 --> 00:23:32,569
When I turned on my phone,

522
00:23:32,570 --> 00:23:34,970
I just saw the message from the court.

523
00:23:35,690 --> 00:23:38,249
And that lawyer, that young lady,

524
00:23:38,250 --> 00:23:39,929
where did she go?

525
00:23:39,930 --> 00:23:41,929
She took care of Xiaolongbao

526
00:23:41,930 --> 00:23:43,690
all night.

527
00:23:44,090 --> 00:23:45,249
She went back to the firm.

528
00:23:45,250 --> 00:23:46,729
Please thank her for me.

529
00:23:46,730 --> 00:23:47,809
Thank you so much.

530
00:23:47,810 --> 00:23:49,369
Thank you, thank you all.

531
00:23:49,370 --> 00:23:51,410
It's nothing. This is what we should do.

532
00:23:54,650 --> 00:23:56,729
Those two useless parents.

533
00:23:56,730 --> 00:23:59,129
Our Xiaolongbao is such a good girl.

534
00:23:59,130 --> 00:24:01,210
I'm here, don't be afraid.

535
00:24:01,410 --> 00:24:02,730
How could they

536
00:24:02,810 --> 00:24:04,809
be so heartless?

537
00:24:04,810 --> 00:24:07,090
My baby, where's my baby?

538
00:24:07,330 --> 00:24:08,369
My baby.

539
00:24:08,370 --> 00:24:10,489
Where did you go last night?

540
00:24:10,490 --> 00:24:12,650
Mom was so worried.

541
00:24:12,770 --> 00:24:13,809
I was so worried.

542
00:24:13,810 --> 00:24:15,569
I looked for you all night

543
00:24:15,570 --> 00:24:17,090
and couldn't find you.

544
00:24:17,610 --> 00:24:20,170
Are you hurt anywhere?

545
00:24:20,370 --> 00:24:22,450
Are you hungry?

546
00:24:22,490 --> 00:24:23,769
I was so worried.

547
00:24:23,770 --> 00:24:25,089
You're not hurt, right?

548
00:24:25,090 --> 00:24:26,289
You're okay, right?

549
00:24:26,290 --> 00:24:27,009
That...

550
00:24:27,010 --> 00:24:28,129
What are you doing?

551
00:24:28,130 --> 00:24:30,010
Are you hungry?

552
00:24:31,170 --> 00:24:32,730
Put your phone away.

553
00:24:33,850 --> 00:24:35,770
Filming isn't allowed in court.

554
00:24:37,610 --> 00:24:38,930
Baby.

555
00:24:40,450 --> 00:24:43,650
(Looking down on people.)

556
00:24:44,360 --> 00:24:46,010
(Just a small-time judge.)

557
00:24:46,370 --> 00:24:48,330
(Do you think your jurisdiction
is the Pacific Ocean?)

558
00:24:48,450 --> 00:24:50,970
(Like the whole world
revolves around you?)

559
00:24:51,090 --> 00:24:52,930
(So full of yourself.)

560
00:25:29,650 --> 00:25:30,770
No...

561
00:25:44,650 --> 00:25:45,930
Bad guy!

562
00:26:48,930 --> 00:26:50,949
(Stay calm. I'm sorry.
Please contact me for compensation.)

563
00:26:50,950 --> 00:26:52,679
(Don't be upset. Accidents happen.)

564
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:54,210
(Hehe. Qin...)

565
00:27:01,330 --> 00:27:03,650
(Miss Liu)

566
00:27:10,650 --> 00:27:13,050
(Jindian Law Firm)

567
00:27:16,090 --> 00:27:18,489
He transferred all of his parents' property
into your name alone.

568
00:27:18,490 --> 00:27:20,890
- Does that mean it should go to you?
- Shouldn't it go to me?

569
00:27:20,930 --> 00:27:22,209
Why should it go to you?

570
00:27:22,210 --> 00:27:23,730
Why not?

571
00:27:23,890 --> 00:27:25,089
Do you even make sense?

572
00:27:25,090 --> 00:27:26,329
- What do you mean?
- Sit down.

573
00:27:26,330 --> 00:27:28,050
You're the one being unreasonable.

574
00:27:35,330 --> 00:27:36,449
Call the bailiff.

575
00:27:36,450 --> 00:27:37,970
I didn't.

576
00:27:39,610 --> 00:27:40,189
Look at him.

577
00:27:40,190 --> 00:27:40,929
Is that how you act?

578
00:27:40,930 --> 00:27:42,810
That's not what happened.

579
00:27:44,330 --> 00:27:45,570
Calm down.

580
00:27:57,890 --> 00:28:00,170
(Hearing in progress)

581
00:28:02,090 --> 00:28:04,050
My head is buzzing right now.

582
00:28:08,010 --> 00:28:10,330
Do you think
I've got some serious illness?

583
00:28:12,290 --> 00:28:14,249
After taking in
so much emotional garbage,

584
00:28:14,250 --> 00:28:15,969
feeling dizzy, nauseous,
wanting to throw up,

585
00:28:15,970 --> 00:28:17,450
that's all normal.

586
00:28:17,930 --> 00:28:19,289
You make it sound like

587
00:28:19,290 --> 00:28:21,370
we're some kind of dumping ground.

588
00:28:22,050 --> 00:28:24,129
Don't make it sound so noble.

589
00:28:24,130 --> 00:28:25,489
Emotional garbage

590
00:28:25,490 --> 00:28:28,090
has no value at all.

591
00:28:29,930 --> 00:28:31,329
(Qingcheng District
People's Court, Tianhai City)

592
00:28:31,330 --> 00:28:32,849
I'm already out.

593
00:28:32,850 --> 00:28:34,450
Heading over now.

594
00:28:34,570 --> 00:28:35,329
I checked.

595
00:28:35,330 --> 00:28:37,410
The flight will land
on time. It won't be late.

596
00:28:37,850 --> 00:28:39,050
Don't worry.

597
00:28:40,010 --> 00:28:41,290
I'll hang up now.

598
00:29:06,250 --> 00:29:09,590
(I'm sorry. Please contact me for compensation.
Don't be upset. Accidents happen.)

599
00:29:16,170 --> 00:29:17,490
Your phone.

600
00:29:17,690 --> 00:29:19,170
Answer it for me.

601
00:29:22,490 --> 00:29:23,580
Hello.

602
00:29:23,890 --> 00:29:26,810
I'm the owner of the car
with plate number 3596S.

603
00:29:27,410 --> 00:29:29,569
You left a note on my car.

604
00:29:29,570 --> 00:29:31,050
My side mirror.

605
00:29:31,370 --> 00:29:32,490
Quick.

606
00:29:35,650 --> 00:29:36,850
Shen Xie...

607
00:29:40,050 --> 00:29:41,250
Hello.

608
00:29:41,730 --> 00:29:43,090
May I ask your surname?

609
00:29:43,130 --> 00:29:43,929
My surname is Shen.

610
00:29:43,930 --> 00:29:45,609
Hello, Mr. Shen.

611
00:29:45,610 --> 00:29:47,330
I'm really sorry.

612
00:29:47,570 --> 00:29:49,010
Today,

613
00:29:49,170 --> 00:29:50,730
while passing by your car,

614
00:29:50,810 --> 00:29:53,130
I accidentally knocked off
the side mirror.

615
00:29:53,610 --> 00:29:55,009
You hit it while driving?

616
00:29:55,010 --> 00:29:56,409
Which insurance company are you with?

617
00:29:56,410 --> 00:29:58,009
Are we going through insurance or what?

618
00:29:58,010 --> 00:30:00,410
No. I was walking.

619
00:30:00,450 --> 00:30:01,449
Walking?

620
00:30:01,450 --> 00:30:03,090
You knocked it off while walking?

621
00:30:06,010 --> 00:30:07,369
Walking, yes.

622
00:30:07,370 --> 00:30:08,809
I was just walking,

623
00:30:08,810 --> 00:30:10,130
I...

624
00:30:10,450 --> 00:30:11,689
Drinking water.

625
00:30:11,690 --> 00:30:12,849
Right.

626
00:30:12,850 --> 00:30:14,570
I threw the bottle,

627
00:30:17,690 --> 00:30:18,889
kicked it,

628
00:30:18,890 --> 00:30:20,290
and twisted my ankle.

629
00:30:20,770 --> 00:30:22,850
My foot hurt.

630
00:30:22,890 --> 00:30:24,609
It really hurt.

631
00:30:24,610 --> 00:30:25,769
It hurt.

632
00:30:25,770 --> 00:30:26,970
So I...

633
00:30:29,690 --> 00:30:31,610
The downward force...

634
00:30:32,130 --> 00:30:34,049
I just

635
00:30:34,050 --> 00:30:35,569
pulled the side mirror

636
00:30:35,570 --> 00:30:36,930
off.

637
00:30:38,810 --> 00:30:39,930
Alright.

638
00:30:40,810 --> 00:30:42,330
So how do you plan to compensate?

639
00:30:44,650 --> 00:30:45,929
It's our responsibility.

640
00:30:45,930 --> 00:30:47,850
We'll definitely cover it.

641
00:30:48,010 --> 00:30:49,410
Could you tell me

642
00:30:49,690 --> 00:30:52,049
roughly how much the repair will cost?

643
00:30:52,050 --> 00:30:53,290
How about this,

644
00:30:53,450 --> 00:30:55,489
I'll contact the dealership first.

645
00:30:55,490 --> 00:30:57,730
Once I confirm the price, I'll call you.

646
00:31:02,970 --> 00:31:04,650
Look at what you did.

647
00:31:05,650 --> 00:31:08,289
If you say this wasn't deliberate revenge,
I wouldn't believe it.

648
00:31:08,290 --> 00:31:10,410
If you say it was deliberate,

649
00:31:10,530 --> 00:31:12,490
well, maybe just a little.

650
00:31:12,650 --> 00:31:14,970
I helped him out with good intentions,

651
00:31:15,170 --> 00:31:16,369
wasted an entire night

652
00:31:16,370 --> 00:31:17,729
and half my morning.

653
00:31:17,730 --> 00:31:19,490
Not only did he not thank me,

654
00:31:20,130 --> 00:31:22,369
he even said I was using
his name to attract clients.

655
00:31:22,370 --> 00:31:24,489
Tell me, how could I
not feel wronged or angry?

656
00:31:24,490 --> 00:31:25,969
But no matter how angry I was,

657
00:31:25,970 --> 00:31:27,209
I'm still a rational person.

658
00:31:27,210 --> 00:31:28,169
Those first two kicks,

659
00:31:28,170 --> 00:31:29,809
I did use some force.

660
00:31:29,810 --> 00:31:31,249
But what I kicked

661
00:31:31,250 --> 00:31:32,770
was the tire.

662
00:31:33,450 --> 00:31:35,730
The side mirror was definitely
not part of the plan.

663
00:31:36,330 --> 00:31:37,369
Besides,

664
00:31:37,370 --> 00:31:38,329
his car looked

665
00:31:38,330 --> 00:31:39,809
pretty expensive.

666
00:31:39,810 --> 00:31:40,969
How could it just

667
00:31:40,970 --> 00:31:42,290
fall off

668
00:31:42,370 --> 00:31:43,770
like that?

669
00:31:45,490 --> 00:31:47,970
Well, maybe you're just stronger.

670
00:31:48,530 --> 00:31:50,610
Now I don't even know

671
00:31:50,970 --> 00:31:53,530
if a thousand will cover it.

672
00:31:53,890 --> 00:31:56,089
I don't even know
how I'll manage food this month.

673
00:31:56,090 --> 00:31:58,090
Alright, enough of that.

674
00:31:58,570 --> 00:32:00,770
I'll cover your rent for next month.

675
00:32:00,850 --> 00:32:02,650
You pay me back the month after.

676
00:32:03,330 --> 00:32:04,490
Then,

677
00:32:04,770 --> 00:32:07,170
lend me another two hundred?

678
00:32:08,290 --> 00:32:10,329
Eating still doesn't shut you up.

679
00:32:10,330 --> 00:32:11,770
Eat more.

680
00:32:15,690 --> 00:32:17,130
Thank you, Lian.

681
00:32:22,890 --> 00:32:26,090
Food's here.

682
00:32:30,050 --> 00:32:31,650
What is this?

683
00:32:31,890 --> 00:32:33,729
This is my newly invented dish.

684
00:32:33,730 --> 00:32:35,129
Try it.

685
00:32:35,130 --> 00:32:36,769
That looks awful.

686
00:32:36,770 --> 00:32:37,849
How is it awful?

687
00:32:37,850 --> 00:32:39,929
It's century egg mixed with eggplant.

688
00:32:39,930 --> 00:32:41,569
There was nothing else
left in the fridge,

689
00:32:41,570 --> 00:32:43,130
so I just made do.

690
00:32:43,210 --> 00:32:45,370
It's actually not bad. Try it.

691
00:32:46,330 --> 00:32:49,610
Go on, don't be picky.

692
00:32:52,290 --> 00:32:53,450
Fine.

693
00:32:54,610 --> 00:32:55,689
I can't bring myself to eat it.

694
00:32:55,690 --> 00:32:57,650
You try it.

695
00:32:59,130 --> 00:33:01,170
You don't even dare eat my cooking?

696
00:33:04,330 --> 00:33:05,449
Well?

697
00:33:05,450 --> 00:33:07,129
If I close my eyes, it's okay.

698
00:33:07,130 --> 00:33:09,089
See, I told you.

699
00:33:09,090 --> 00:33:10,809
Trust my cooking.

700
00:33:10,810 --> 00:33:12,050
Have some more.

701
00:33:12,970 --> 00:33:14,329
Only with your eyes closed.

702
00:33:14,330 --> 00:33:15,409
It's so good.

703
00:33:15,410 --> 00:33:18,090
You just don't get it.

704
00:33:18,650 --> 00:33:19,649
It's actually pretty good.

705
00:33:19,650 --> 00:33:21,689
Feels like a five star chef made it.

706
00:33:21,690 --> 00:33:22,889
Right?

707
00:33:22,890 --> 00:33:24,330
I think it's good.

708
00:33:24,490 --> 00:33:25,289
Have some more.

709
00:33:25,290 --> 00:33:26,970
Then add more chili sauce.

710
00:33:30,170 --> 00:33:31,289
Why?

711
00:33:31,290 --> 00:33:33,049
My stomach feels off.

712
00:33:33,050 --> 00:33:34,410
I feel like throwing up.

713
00:33:34,690 --> 00:33:36,050
My stomach hurts.

714
00:33:36,290 --> 00:33:37,570
You're pregnant?

715
00:33:37,650 --> 00:33:39,169
What are you talking about?

716
00:33:39,170 --> 00:33:41,489
My stomach really hurts, I'm not joking.

717
00:33:41,490 --> 00:33:43,409
- I'm going to the restroom.
- Trying to scam me?

718
00:33:43,410 --> 00:33:44,529
My dish was perfectly fine.

719
00:33:44,530 --> 00:33:46,370
It's not because of your dish.

720
00:33:46,530 --> 00:33:47,729
I'm not talking about you.

721
00:33:47,730 --> 00:33:49,649
I mean Shen Xiezhi's sashimi.

722
00:33:49,650 --> 00:33:51,090
That's more like it.

723
00:34:03,610 --> 00:34:05,730
You still dare to call me?

724
00:34:05,930 --> 00:34:07,089
What is it?

725
00:34:07,090 --> 00:34:08,290
Ms. Qin.

726
00:34:08,330 --> 00:34:10,369
Thank you so much for last night,

727
00:34:10,370 --> 00:34:12,129
you and Judge Shen.

728
00:34:12,130 --> 00:34:13,000
It's a good thing we had you both.

729
00:34:13,000 --> 00:34:14,929
I knew you were someone
with a sense of justice.

730
00:34:14,930 --> 00:34:16,809
Choosing you as my lawyer
was the right call.

731
00:34:16,810 --> 00:34:18,369
Didn't I already tell you?

732
00:34:18,370 --> 00:34:19,649
I'm not taking your case.

733
00:34:19,650 --> 00:34:21,249
No, Ms. Qin, please listen to me.

734
00:34:21,250 --> 00:34:22,009
Please hear me out.

735
00:34:22,010 --> 00:34:23,009
That...

736
00:34:23,010 --> 00:34:24,089
I promise,

737
00:34:24,090 --> 00:34:25,889
I promise I'll treat the child well.

738
00:34:25,890 --> 00:34:27,209
Besides, even if you don't trust me,

739
00:34:27,210 --> 00:34:29,010
don't you trust her grandmother?

740
00:34:31,690 --> 00:34:33,570
If you really don't take the case,

741
00:34:34,050 --> 00:34:35,970
the child will be awarded to her mother.

742
00:34:36,130 --> 00:34:38,169
Do you think my ex wife is reliable?

743
00:34:38,170 --> 00:34:39,529
As for when I'll remarry,

744
00:34:39,530 --> 00:34:40,529
that's uncertain.

745
00:34:40,530 --> 00:34:41,930
But she's about

746
00:34:42,090 --> 00:34:43,570
to get married soon.

747
00:34:54,850 --> 00:34:56,849
Xiezhi, why did you take a taxi?

748
00:34:56,850 --> 00:34:58,289
The side mirror was broken off.

749
00:34:58,290 --> 00:35:00,170
Was it retaliation from a party?

750
00:35:00,370 --> 00:35:01,690
Not really.

751
00:35:01,770 --> 00:35:02,729
Probably just an accident.

752
00:35:02,730 --> 00:35:05,250
You've been in
the family division for a while now.

753
00:35:05,650 --> 00:35:06,970
What have you gained?

754
00:35:10,050 --> 00:35:11,729
I just feel that

755
00:35:11,730 --> 00:35:13,889
after all these years
of legal education,

756
00:35:13,890 --> 00:35:16,369
after going through
so many rigorous exams,

757
00:35:16,370 --> 00:35:17,449
in the end,

758
00:35:17,450 --> 00:35:19,169
it all comes down
to sitting in a mediation room

759
00:35:19,170 --> 00:35:22,210
and acting as
an emotional dumping ground

760
00:35:22,650 --> 00:35:23,969
for all these clients breaking down.

761
00:35:23,970 --> 00:35:25,970
It's not that I'm unwilling to do it.

762
00:35:26,050 --> 00:35:27,209
I just don't understand

763
00:35:27,210 --> 00:35:29,489
what all that effort back then was for.

764
00:35:29,490 --> 00:35:32,849
These clients can't wait to pull you in and
unload everything that's happened to them

765
00:35:32,850 --> 00:35:35,049
over so many years,

766
00:35:35,050 --> 00:35:36,529
all the old grievances.

767
00:35:36,530 --> 00:35:39,370
Who's right and who's wrong,
isn't it obvious at a glance?

768
00:35:39,890 --> 00:35:42,130
Why use a sledgehammer
to crack a nut, right?

769
00:35:42,170 --> 00:35:44,850
Looks like your dad misjudged again.

770
00:35:45,850 --> 00:35:47,129
If he expected me

771
00:35:47,130 --> 00:35:49,609
to have my whole worldview overturned
in a grassroots family court,

772
00:35:49,610 --> 00:35:51,610
then he's bound to be disappointed.

773
00:35:51,650 --> 00:35:52,889
These past few days

774
00:35:52,890 --> 00:35:56,049
have only confirmed
what I've always believed.

775
00:35:56,050 --> 00:35:57,089
For a professional judge,

776
00:35:57,090 --> 00:36:00,129
the most important quality
is objectivity and composure,

777
00:36:00,130 --> 00:36:02,489
not so-called deep empathy.

778
00:36:02,490 --> 00:36:03,409
In my view,

779
00:36:03,410 --> 00:36:05,769
getting too involved

780
00:36:05,770 --> 00:36:07,889
only makes you as conflicted and lost

781
00:36:07,890 --> 00:36:08,889
as the parties themselves.

782
00:36:08,890 --> 00:36:10,049
Keeping a proper distance

783
00:36:10,050 --> 00:36:11,729
is the only way to stay clear-headed

784
00:36:11,730 --> 00:36:13,609
and arrive at the best solution.

785
00:36:13,610 --> 00:36:16,249
My dad's been out
of frontline work too long.

786
00:36:16,250 --> 00:36:18,689
He's still living in his own
idealized memories.

787
00:36:18,690 --> 00:36:20,489
He's clinging to outdated ideas,

788
00:36:20,490 --> 00:36:21,489
trying to force me

789
00:36:21,490 --> 00:36:24,009
into the mold he once set,

790
00:36:24,010 --> 00:36:26,290
grasping at something
that no longer exists.

791
00:36:27,970 --> 00:36:30,729
Then you should reason with him,
try to convince him.

792
00:36:30,730 --> 00:36:32,289
Convince him?

793
00:36:32,290 --> 00:36:33,689
You know what he's like.

794
00:36:33,690 --> 00:36:35,729
I'd have better luck
convincing the earth

795
00:36:35,730 --> 00:36:37,570
to spin westward.

796
00:36:40,810 --> 00:36:43,969
Can't even handle something
as simple as family matters.

797
00:36:43,970 --> 00:36:46,170
Looks like my eldest grandson's

798
00:36:46,410 --> 00:36:47,770
professional ability
is questionable too.

799
00:36:49,290 --> 00:36:50,249
Grandpa,

800
00:36:50,250 --> 00:36:52,810
after all that,
you're taking a jab at me.

801
00:36:55,210 --> 00:36:58,770
If you can't manage your own household,
how can you manage the world?

802
00:37:02,570 --> 00:37:05,330
My approach to family disputes is

803
00:37:05,370 --> 00:37:06,729
contain the conflict,

804
00:37:06,730 --> 00:37:08,329
seek common ground
while reserving differences,

805
00:37:08,330 --> 00:37:11,010
part ways peacefully and move on.

806
00:37:11,650 --> 00:37:14,810
That doesn't quite align
with the current direction

807
00:37:15,210 --> 00:37:16,570
of judicial practice.

808
00:37:17,090 --> 00:37:19,449
There are mediation targets to meet.

809
00:37:19,450 --> 00:37:21,689
Can't I be a bit flexible
with my own family matters?

810
00:37:21,690 --> 00:37:23,440
Are you going to make life hard
for your grandson too?

811
00:37:23,440 --> 00:37:24,529
Alright, my dear grandson.

812
00:37:24,530 --> 00:37:25,489
I'll drop it.

813
00:37:25,490 --> 00:37:27,170
I won't bring it up anymore.

814
00:37:38,370 --> 00:37:39,289
(Every week,)

815
00:37:39,290 --> 00:37:40,329
(Monday, Wednesday, Friday,)

816
00:37:40,330 --> 00:37:41,689
(the child stays with me.)

817
00:37:41,690 --> 00:37:43,849
(Tuesday, Thursday, Saturday, with her.)

818
00:37:43,850 --> 00:37:45,889
(Tuesday, Thursday, Saturday with me,
Wednesday, Friday, Sunday with you.)

819
00:37:45,890 --> 00:37:47,369
(Monday has the least traffic,)

820
00:37:47,370 --> 00:37:48,089
(we split it evenly.)

821
00:37:48,090 --> 00:37:49,729
(Deal? What do you think?)

822
00:37:49,730 --> 00:37:52,290
(I promise I'll treat the child well.)

823
00:37:52,370 --> 00:37:53,689
(Even if you don't trust me,)

824
00:37:53,690 --> 00:37:55,450
(don't you trust her grandmother?)

825
00:37:55,730 --> 00:37:57,650
(I want Mom.)

826
00:38:15,610 --> 00:38:17,130
Xiaolongbao.

827
00:38:17,410 --> 00:38:19,970
It's not that I don't want
to take you home.

828
00:38:20,370 --> 00:38:22,409
I can barely take care of myself.

829
00:38:22,410 --> 00:38:24,050
How could I take care of you too?

830
00:38:24,450 --> 00:38:26,490
Xiaolongbao, so you're hungry too.

831
00:38:26,610 --> 00:38:28,210
Let's go get something good to eat.

832
00:38:28,570 --> 00:38:29,969
Trust me.

833
00:38:29,970 --> 00:38:32,650
Kids are full of potential.

834
00:38:41,690 --> 00:38:43,569
Let's wash your face nice and clean,

835
00:38:43,570 --> 00:38:44,729
and you'll be our cute,

836
00:38:44,730 --> 00:38:47,090
pretty Xiaolongbao again.

837
00:38:49,890 --> 00:38:51,689
From now on,
let's smile like this, okay?

838
00:38:51,690 --> 00:38:52,769
No matter what happens,

839
00:38:52,770 --> 00:38:53,849
just like before,

840
00:38:53,850 --> 00:38:55,289
stay positive and smile.

841
00:38:55,290 --> 00:38:56,850
Face everything with a smile.

842
00:39:16,290 --> 00:39:17,490
Le.

843
00:39:17,530 --> 00:39:18,249
How are you?

844
00:39:18,250 --> 00:39:18,809
Le.

845
00:39:18,810 --> 00:39:19,449
I'm fine.

846
00:39:19,450 --> 00:39:20,690
Le.

847
00:39:21,170 --> 00:39:22,320
Le, are you okay?

848
00:39:22,320 --> 00:39:24,000
- You scared us yesterday.
- It's all fine now.

849
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:25,409
Yeah, really scared us.

850
00:39:25,410 --> 00:39:26,489
I'm fine.

851
00:39:26,490 --> 00:39:28,290
I'm already better.

852
00:39:28,890 --> 00:39:31,769
You know how strong I am.

853
00:39:31,770 --> 00:39:33,810
Of course I'm fine.

854
00:39:33,930 --> 00:39:36,530
I thought you'd rest
at home a bit longer.

855
00:39:37,050 --> 00:39:39,570
Look at that serious face.

856
00:39:39,690 --> 00:39:41,810
I thought court was in session.

857
00:39:45,490 --> 00:39:48,290
I came back to work

858
00:39:48,810 --> 00:39:50,410
with the doctor's approval.

859
00:39:51,850 --> 00:39:53,449
I'm really fine.

860
00:39:53,450 --> 00:39:54,569
Go on, get to work.

861
00:39:54,570 --> 00:39:55,849
I'm really fine, don't worry.

862
00:39:55,850 --> 00:39:57,049
Are you sure, Le?

863
00:39:57,050 --> 00:39:58,529
Then take care.

864
00:39:58,530 --> 00:40:01,489
Alright.

865
00:40:01,490 --> 00:40:02,969
- If you feel unwell, tell us.
- Go on now.

866
00:40:02,970 --> 00:40:04,210
Okay.

867
00:40:05,210 --> 00:40:06,009
Now,

868
00:40:06,010 --> 00:40:08,690
please rise for the presiding judge
and panel judges.

869
00:40:08,730 --> 00:40:10,209
Reporting to the presiding judge,
all parties

870
00:40:10,210 --> 00:40:11,849
and their legal representatives
are present.

871
00:40:11,850 --> 00:40:13,210
Pre-hearing preparations are complete.

872
00:40:13,410 --> 00:40:14,810
We may proceed.

873
00:40:16,450 --> 00:40:17,449
Court is now in session.

874
00:40:17,450 --> 00:40:18,289
(Hearing in progress)

875
00:40:18,290 --> 00:40:20,089
I really know I was wrong.

876
00:40:20,090 --> 00:40:21,810
You know what happened?

877
00:40:21,890 --> 00:40:24,210
My account got banned.

878
00:40:24,410 --> 00:40:26,249
Right now I rely entirely
on that account's income

879
00:40:26,250 --> 00:40:27,409
to support me and my daughter.

880
00:40:27,410 --> 00:40:28,689
If the account is gone,

881
00:40:28,690 --> 00:40:29,569
then my daughter and I

882
00:40:29,570 --> 00:40:31,249
will have nothing to live on.

883
00:40:31,250 --> 00:40:32,970
I was anxious, so...

884
00:40:33,050 --> 00:40:34,449
But then I thought,

885
00:40:34,450 --> 00:40:35,880
her father is here too.

886
00:40:35,880 --> 00:40:37,129
He can't just ignore the child, right?

887
00:40:37,130 --> 00:40:39,089
Who knew Liu Wenbo

888
00:40:39,090 --> 00:40:40,729
would just walk away.

889
00:40:40,730 --> 00:40:42,810
Keep acting, go on.

890
00:40:43,010 --> 00:40:44,329
Look at your poor acting.

891
00:40:44,330 --> 00:40:46,370
Do you think everyone here is a fool?

892
00:40:47,010 --> 00:40:48,289
Presiding judge, why don't you ask her,

893
00:40:48,290 --> 00:40:49,769
ask her what she was doing that day,

894
00:40:49,770 --> 00:40:51,120
how she ended up
leaving the child behind.

895
00:40:51,120 --> 00:40:51,969
I...

896
00:40:51,970 --> 00:40:54,130
If you won't say it, I will.

897
00:40:54,690 --> 00:40:57,370
You went to those so-called big shots
to fix your problem, right?

898
00:40:58,410 --> 00:40:59,969
To get your account unbanned.

899
00:40:59,970 --> 00:41:00,969
And now that same person

900
00:41:00,970 --> 00:41:01,969
is telling you

901
00:41:01,970 --> 00:41:03,769
to play the sympathy card

902
00:41:03,770 --> 00:41:04,729
to save your account.

903
00:41:04,730 --> 00:41:05,489
So now,

904
00:41:05,490 --> 00:41:07,529
my daughter suddenly
becomes your precious child again.

905
00:41:07,530 --> 00:41:10,129
Aren't you her father too?
Why don't you take care of her?

906
00:41:10,130 --> 00:41:11,489
Don't change the subject.

907
00:41:11,490 --> 00:41:13,970
The issue happened
while the child was with you.

908
00:41:15,130 --> 00:41:16,880
Sun Lala, isn't your backer so capable?

909
00:41:16,880 --> 00:41:18,320
Then how about this,
have him pay two million.

910
00:41:18,320 --> 00:41:19,560
Then you can have the child.

911
00:41:19,560 --> 00:41:21,089
Is that even something
a human would say?

912
00:41:21,090 --> 00:41:22,250
You dare?

913
00:41:22,490 --> 00:41:23,969
You are so bad.

914
00:41:23,970 --> 00:41:25,289
Let me tell both of you,

915
00:41:25,290 --> 00:41:27,449
whoever dares mistreat
my granddaughter again,

916
00:41:27,450 --> 00:41:28,969
I'll risk my life against you.

917
00:41:28,970 --> 00:41:30,810
I mean it.

918
00:41:31,650 --> 00:41:32,729
Mom, I was just saying.

919
00:41:32,730 --> 00:41:34,449
Does she even have that kind of money?

920
00:41:34,450 --> 00:41:36,129
(Presiding Judge)

921
00:41:36,130 --> 00:41:37,529
No talking in the gallery.

922
00:41:37,530 --> 00:41:39,170
Grandma Liu, please stay calm.

923
00:41:39,970 --> 00:41:41,129
Madam,

924
00:41:41,130 --> 00:41:42,449
please don't get too worked up.

925
00:41:42,450 --> 00:41:44,089
If something happens to you,

926
00:41:44,090 --> 00:41:46,649
your precious son will still be counting
on your savings to get by.

927
00:41:46,650 --> 00:41:48,369
What kind of thing are you saying?

928
00:41:48,370 --> 00:41:49,129
Your Honor,

929
00:41:49,130 --> 00:41:50,249
just look at Liu Wenbo.

930
00:41:50,250 --> 00:41:52,449
He doesn't want the child at all.

931
00:41:52,450 --> 00:41:54,800
He's using the child
as a bargaining chip,

932
00:41:54,800 --> 00:41:55,920
treating this like a business deal.

933
00:41:55,920 --> 00:41:57,169
We don't want any money.

934
00:41:57,170 --> 00:41:58,529
Your Honors, we don't want a cent.

935
00:41:58,530 --> 00:41:59,649
We don't want anything.

936
00:41:59,650 --> 00:42:00,969
I just want my granddaughter.

937
00:42:00,970 --> 00:42:02,809
I can raise her.

938
00:42:02,810 --> 00:42:04,209
Mom, why refuse the money?

939
00:42:04,210 --> 00:42:05,329
She should pay that.

940
00:42:05,330 --> 00:42:06,890
That's child support.

941
00:42:32,570 --> 00:42:34,370
Enough.

942
00:42:34,730 --> 00:42:35,489
Alright.

943
00:42:35,490 --> 00:42:37,209
The court has understood the positions

944
00:42:37,210 --> 00:42:38,569
and requests of both parties.

945
00:42:38,570 --> 00:42:39,089
The court...

946
00:42:39,090 --> 00:42:40,209
Presiding judge,

947
00:42:40,210 --> 00:42:41,690
I have something to say.

948
00:42:42,090 --> 00:42:43,250
Go ahead.

949
00:42:43,410 --> 00:42:45,169
After several hearings,

950
00:42:45,170 --> 00:42:48,850
I believe the judges
can all see that Ms. Sun Lala

951
00:42:48,930 --> 00:42:50,809
is not a qualified mother.

952
00:42:50,810 --> 00:42:52,330
Who do you think you are?

953
00:42:52,490 --> 00:42:53,929
Are you the judge?

954
00:42:53,930 --> 00:42:55,290
Defendant,

955
00:42:55,570 --> 00:42:56,810
do not interrupt.

956
00:42:58,450 --> 00:42:59,009
Of course,

957
00:42:59,010 --> 00:43:00,849
my client Mr. Liu Wenbo

958
00:43:00,850 --> 00:43:02,970
is also not a qualified father.

959
00:43:14,620 --> 00:43:18,080
♪All the little things
between you and me♪

960
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,760
♪Woven into our lives♪

961
00:43:21,610 --> 00:43:23,590
♪The building blocks of life♪

962
00:43:23,590 --> 00:43:25,290
♪Shape the sky above us♪

963
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:27,450
♪Are you doing alright?♪

964
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:30,450
♪What are you struggling for?♪

965
00:43:31,330 --> 00:43:35,150
♪Some questions weigh like mountains♪

966
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:40,380
♪How do we piece life back together?♪

967
00:43:40,940 --> 00:43:45,130
♪So hate can fade
and love feels new again♪

968
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:48,200
♪Reclaim the barren parts of life♪

969
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:54,570
♪Walking this road
together, still hoping♪

970
00:43:55,360 --> 00:44:00,420
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

971
00:44:00,720 --> 00:44:04,690
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

972
00:44:04,920 --> 00:44:09,900
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

973
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:14,880
♪Where fairness stands♪

974
00:44:15,350 --> 00:44:17,590
♪Within every heart♪

975
00:44:17,590 --> 00:44:20,240
♪So many voices calling♪

976
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:24,790
♪Struggling, lost,
waiting for an answer♪

977
00:44:24,790 --> 00:44:27,140
♪Light up the lamps♪

978
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:29,810
♪To answer those voices♪

979
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,240
♪You deserve to be happy♪

980
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:34,990
♪Loud and clear♪

981
00:44:34,990 --> 00:44:37,310
♪All the little things♪

982
00:44:37,310 --> 00:44:40,010
♪Woven into our lives♪

983
00:44:40,830 --> 00:44:42,880
♪The building blocks of life♪

984
00:44:42,880 --> 00:44:44,590
♪Shape the sky above us♪

985
00:44:44,590 --> 00:44:47,040
♪Are you doing alright?♪

986
00:44:47,040 --> 00:44:49,150
♪What are you struggling for?♪

987
00:44:49,400 --> 00:44:51,530
♪Some questions♪

988
00:44:52,100 --> 00:44:54,800
♪Weigh like mountains♪

989
00:44:57,690 --> 00:45:02,840
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

990
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:07,130
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

991
00:45:07,310 --> 00:45:12,360
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

992
00:45:12,730 --> 00:45:16,430
♪Where fairness stands♪

993
00:45:16,600 --> 00:45:19,680
♪Within the law♪

994
00:45:20,840 --> 00:45:29,520
♪And within every heart♪
